Business Brief -- Pier 1 Imports Inc.:
   Agreements Reached to Sell
   Portion of Sunbelt Holding
Pier 1, a specialty retailer, said it is selling the
shares to a money management arm of Smith Barney, Harris
Upham  Co., which will hold them in investment accounts.
   Pier 1 sold about 43% of Sunbelt in a public offering late
last year at $8.50 a share, leaving it with a 56.7% stake.
   In American Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Sunbelt closed at $7.125, down 37.5 cents. Pier 1 closed at
10.375, down 25 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite
trading.